The 2021 U.S. Women's Championship is a 12-player round-robin featuring the strongest female players in the USA, who compete for USD $100,000 in prize money and the title of 2019 U.S. Women's Champion. If two or more players tie for first place a playoff will be held.

Players receive 90 minutes for the first 40 moves followed by 30 minutes for the rest of the game, with a 30-second increment from move one. Draw offers are not allowed before move 30. Official website: uschesschamps.com
